{{notability|Companies|date=December 2014}} The '''Institut für Dokumentologie und Editorik''' (IDE - Institute for Documentology and Scholarly Editing) is a German association (with the legal status of "[[Eingetragener Verein]]") of researchers working on the application of digital methods to historical documents. Fields of interest include digitization, [[Transcription (linguistics)|transcription]], text encoding, [[textual criticism]], critical scholarly editing, digital [[palaeography]], and digital [[codicology]]. It was established in 2006 and has contributed in several ways to the field of [[digital humanities]] and has organized Summer Schools on a regular basis at various universities in Germany and Austria (Berlin, Chemnitz, Cologne, Rostock, Vienna).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.i-d-e.de/aktivitaeten/schools/ |title=Schools |publisher=Institut für Dokumentologie und Editorik}}</ref> Most notably, the IDE publishes the series ''Schriften des Instituts für Dokumentologie und Editorik''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.i-d-e.de/publikationen/schriften/ |title=Schriftenreihe |publisher=Institut für Dokumentologie und Editorik}}</ref> distributed in print and freely online.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kups.ub.uni-koeln.de/4337/ |title=Kodikologie und Paläographie im digitalen Zeitalter 2 - Codicology and Palaeography in the Digital Age 2 |work=uni-koeln.de}}</ref> The IDE supports [[open access]]. The series is discussed and reviewed in German<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sehepunkte.de/2009/03/14673.html |title=SEHEPUNKTE - Rezension von: Digital ist besser - Ausgabe 9 (2009), Nr. 3 |work=sehepunkte.de}}</ref><ref> A. Mentzel-Reuters, [[Deutsches Archiv für Erforschung des Mittelalters]] 66 (2010), 109-136.</ref><ref>Wout Dillen, Bibliothek Forschung und Praxis 38/1 (2014), 156-160, doi 10.1515/bfp-2014-0009</ref> and international journals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalmedievalist.org/journal/6/tarte/ |title=DM 6 (2010) Rehbein, Malte, Patrick Sahle, and Torsten Schaßan, eds. 2009. Kodikologie und Paläographie im digitalen Zeitalter, Codicology and Palaeography in the Digital Age. Norderstedt: BoD. |work=digitalmedievalist.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://ancientworldonline.blogspot.com/2011/09/open-access-publictions-from-institut.html |title=AWOL - The Ancient World Online |author=Charles Jones |work=ancientworldonline.blogspot.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalmedievalist.org/journal/8/garces/ |title=DM 8 (2012) Franz Fischer, Christiane Fritze, and Georg Vogeler, eds. 2010. Kodikologie und Paläographie im digitalen Zeitalter 2, Codicology and Palaeography in the Digital Age 2, Norderstedt: BoD. |work=digitalmedievalist.org}}</ref>
Since July 2014 the IDE also publishes the [[open access journal]] ''RIDE: A Review Journal for Digital Editions and Resources''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Official website |work=RIDE: A Review Journal for Digital Editions and Resources |publisher=Institut für Dokumentologie und Editorik |accessdate=2014-12-13 |url=http://ride.i-d-e.de/}}</ref>
