The [[France|French]] '''''airborne nuclear warheads (TN81)''''' is a [[Thermonuclear weapon|thermonuclear warhead]] carried by the [[Air-Sol Moyenne Portée (ASMP)]] medium-range [[air-to-surface missile]], a component of the [[Force de frappe]] French nuclear deterrent. The warhead was introduced in 1988. By 1991, 80 warheads had been produced.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Norris|first1=Robert S.|last2=Arkin|first2=William M.|last3=Kristensen
|first3=Hans M.|last4=Handler|first4=Joshua|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-76627280.html|title=French Nuclear Forces, 2001|work=[[Bulletin of the Atomic Scientists]]|date=1 July 2001|accessdate=24 June 2015|subscription=yes|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}}</ref>

Deployment: 60 warheads carried by the ASMP equipping the 60 [[Dassault Mirage 2000N/2000D|Mirage 2000 N]] with the French Air Force and 20 [[Super Etendard]] of Naval Aviation. Each TN81 has a declared destructive power of 300 kilotonnes. This amounts to over 20 times the power of the bomb that destroyed Hiroshima on 6 August 1945 and caused some 250 000 deaths then or in the aftermath.

It has been replaced by 54 [[TNA (Airborne nuclear warhead)]] [[Thermonuclear weapon|thermonuclear warhead]] carried by the ASMPA equipping the [[Dassault Mirage 2000N/2000D|Mirage 2000 N]] and [[Dassault Rafale]].<ref name="champagne">{{Cite web|last1=|first1=|last2=|first2=|last3=|first3=|last4=|first4=|url=http://www.acdn.net/spip/IMG/article_PDF/Latest-Vintage-from-Champagne-New_a636.pdf|title=Latest Vintage from Champagne: New Rafale jets now carrying new ASMP-A missiles and new TNA nuclear warheads!|work= |date=1 July 2001|accessdate=24 January 2016}}</ref>

Specifications: 
* [[thermonuclear weapon]]
* yield from 100 to 300 [[kiloton]] 
* [[insensitive explosives]]

